  Reading SoftImage files
     The  SDSC  image  library  reads  non-compressed,  or   rle-
     compressed  24-bit  RGB  images  and stores them as IMVFBRGB
     VFB's.

  Writing Microsoft Windows BMP files
     Image library IMVFBRGB VFBs are  written  to  non-compressed
     24-bit  RGB  softimage files.  The files are compressed if a
     compression request is given in the flags table.

     Other image library VFB  types  are  converted  to  IMVFBRGB
     VFB's  prior to being written out.  See the ImFileWrite(3IM)
     man page for details.

ERRORS
     In addition to those listed for  ImFileRead(3IM),  SoftImage
     file reading returns the following error codes:

          IMEUNSUPPORTED   Arrangement of pixels in this file is not supported

